cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel end-to-end neural network architecture for clustering high-dimensional data like images and speech. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Among these, cs.LG is the most likely category as the paper focuses on developing a neural network architecture for clustering. cs.CV is also likely as the paper specifically mentions the application of the proposed method to image data. cs.AI and cs.CL are also possible categories as the paper deals with learning perceptual similarity criteria and clustering based on pairwise labels. Finally, cs.NE is a possible category as the paper proposes a neural network architecture for clustering.
